## 🐛 Bug Report

Hi. I'm having some trouble with data validation on the generated xlsx file, the validation is not applied until I manually go to Data Tab -> Data Validations -> Configuration tab -> and click ok.

Lib version: 4.2.1

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
const ExcelJs = require('exceljs');
const Stream = require('stream');
...

const wb = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
    const ws = wb.addWorksheet('Sheet1');

    const categories = ['fruits', 'vegetables'];
    const fruits = ['apple', 'banana', 'orange'];
    const vegetables = ['onion', 'stems', 'leaves'];

    categories.map((c, index) => {
        ws.getCell(`AA${index + 1}`).value = c; //inserting categories in column 'AA'
    }); //close of 'map' categories
    fruits.map((c, index) => {
        ws.getCell(`AB${index + 1}`).value = c; //inserting fruits in column 'AB'
    }); //close of 'map' fruits
    vegetables.map((c, index) => {
        ws.getCell(`AC${index + 1}`).value = c; //inserting vegetables in column 'AC'
    }); //close of 'map' vegetables
    ws.dataValidations.add("A1", { type: 'list', allowBlank: false, formulae: [`=$AA$1:$AA$${categories.length}`.replace('`', '')], });
    ws.dataValidations.add("B1", { type: 'list', allowBlank: false, formulae: [`=IF(A1="fruits", $AB$1:$AB$${fruits.length}, $AC$1:$AC$${vegetables.length})`], });

const stream = new Stream.PassThrough();
    stream.end(Buffer.from(await Workbook.xlsx.writeBuffer()));
    return stream.pipe(res);
```

## The expected behaviour:

It is expected that the validation occurs when the xlsx file is opened, but it isn't until u manually go to the Data Tab -> Data Validations -> Configuration tab -> and click ok. Then the formulae executes on the cell and the conditional IF occurs


## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):
Maybe u can add a function that applies custom formulae to data validations on document created or loaded, that would be fantastic!

